cc:Work.dc:title: Evolving Object
cc:Work.dc:description:
An evolutionary algorithmas seen from the evolving objects framework: an interative algorithm that manipulates individuals with the help of operators. Implementing an algorithm consists in assembling operator instances, just as building something with Lego blocks.
In green are the operators that are ready to use within EO, in yellow the operators that you may need to implement and in red the evaluator, that you should implement.
